The effect of ERK5 Ser-496 phosphorylation is unclear.
RSK1 Ser-221 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
RSK1 Ser-380 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
The effect of RSK1 Ser-732 phosphorylation is unclear.
eEF2K Ser-398 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
AMPKa2 Thr-172 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
Ret Tyr-1015 phosphorylation inhibits phosphotransferase activity, and regulates cell growth and transcription.
The effect of Ret Tyr-1029 phosphorylation is unclear.
Ret Tyr-1062 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and induces interaction with Crk, DOK6, FRS2, Gab1, IRS1, PIK3R1, PRKCA, RAPGEF1, Shc1, Shc3, and PTPN11 (SHP2).
The effect of Ret Tyr-1090 phosphorylation is unclear.
Ret Tyr-1096 phosphorylation induces interaction with Grb2 and PIK3R1.
Ret Tyr-687 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and induces interaction with PTPN11 (SHP2).
Ret Tyr-806 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and regulates cell growth.
Ret Tyr-809 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and regulates cell growth.
Ret Tyr-826 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
Ret Tyr-900 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.

Ret Tyr-905 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and induces interaction with Vav1. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
Ret Tyr-981 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and induces interaction with Src.

ERK2 Tyr-187 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and induces interaction with ERK2, G-beta 1, GSK3B, KSR, TAE and RSK1, inhibits binding to NFkB-p100, and regulates cell growth, cell motility, cytoskeletal reorganization, transcription, protein conformation, intracellular location, and protein degradation. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
Akt1 Tyr-315 phosphorylation was reported to be stimulatory for phosphotransferase activity, although the precise positioning of this phosphosite is predicted to be inhibitory.
Met Thr-1241 phosphorylation likely to stimulate phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.

Met Tyr-1003 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and induces interaction with Cbl, PTP1B and PTPN2. Phosphorylation regulates cell growth, receptor desensitization, protein stabililzation, and ubquitination.
Met Tyr-1230 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.

Met Tyr-1234 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII. Phosphorylation induces interaction with Grb2, PTPN1 and PTPN2.

Met Tyr-1235 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII. Phosphorylation induces interaction with PTPN1 and PTPN2, and regulates cell growth and motility.
Met Tyr-1349 phosphorylation inhibits phosphotransferase activity, and regulates cell growth, cell motility and molecular association.
Met Tyr-1356 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity, and induces interaction with FAK, Gab1, Grb2, INPPL1 (SHIP2), Met, PI3R1; PLCg1; Ron; Shc1 and Src.
The effect of Met Tyr-1365 phosphorylation is unclear.
The effect of IRE1 Tyr-628 phosphorylation is unclear.
CDK5R1 Ser-91 phosphorylation induces interaction with PJA2.
SIK2 Ser-179 phosphorylation is predicted to be inhibitory for phosphotransferase activity. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop just before catalytic subdomain VIII.
SIK2 Ser-343 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
SIK2 Ser-358 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
SIK2 Ser-90 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.
MEKK6 Thr-806 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity.

ASK1 Thr-838 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and protein interaction inhibition. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
MKK3 Ser-218 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and regulates transcription. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.

MKK3 Thr-222 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and regulates cell cycle progression and transcription. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
MEKK3 Ser-526 phosphorylation stimulates phosphotransferase activity and regulates transcription. This phosphosite is located in the kinase activation loop between catalytic subdomains VII and VIII.
